195
0:08:23.382,000 --> 0:08:24,000
because of the combination of receptors

196
0:08:25.193,000 --> 0:08:27,000
and nerve cells that they trigger,

197
0:08:27.706,000 --> 0:08:28,000
sending messages up to the brain

198
0:08:29.264,000 --> 0:08:31,000
in a combinatorial fashion.

199
0:08:32.17,000 --> 0:08:32,000
But it's a bit more complicated,

200
0:08:33.16,000 --> 0:08:35,000
because each of those 400

201
0:08:35.295,000 --> 0:08:37,000
comes in various variants,

202
0:08:37.446,000 --> 0:08:39,000
and depending which variant you have,

203
0:08:39.517,000 --> 0:08:43,000
you might smell coriander, or cilantro, that herb,

204
0:08:43.699,000 --> 0:08:45,000
either as something delicious and savory

205
0:08:46.317,000 --> 0:08:48,000
or something like soap.

206
0:08:48.491,000 --> 0:08:5,000
So we each have an individual world of smell,

207
0:08:51.177,000 --> 0:08:52,000
and that complicates anything

208
0:08:52.818,000 --> 0:08:54,000
when we're studying smell.

